Armed security operatives on Monday in Abuja chased away the supporters of the leader of Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), Nnamdi Kanu, who thronged the court in solidarity with their leader.  The trial of Kanu, who is facing a fresh 15-count terrorism charge and treasonable felony filed against him by the Nigerian government, was later adjourned to Wednesday.



